        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Yesterday, we <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/desantis-allows-anti-woke-giveaway-to-big-wall-street-donors/\">reported</a> on Ron DeSantis‚Äôs major pension giveaways to private equity firms as those firms‚Äô executives donated to groups helping DeSantis‚Äô election bids. While DeSantis scapegoated ‚Äúwoke‚Äù ESG investing, he oversaw the move of $1 billion of public employees‚Äô retirement funds to high-fee, poor-performing hedge funds managed by major Republican donors. <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/florida-lawmakers-help-desantis-shovel-more-cash-to-wall-street/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">Today, we report</a> on a new bill that would let him give away even more of Florida pensioners‚Äô money and how raising money from Wall Street could put him at odds with a federal pay-to-play rule.</p><p><strong>DeSantis has already been forced to answer questions about our reporting, as seen in video from a press conference that took place yesterday. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/levernews/status/1658654397646389248?s=46&amp;t=uDL5oYASKyXRFQqI-lzkTw\">Click here to watch that exchange</a>.</strong></p>"
